                    hand-sized problems. For larger matrices, numerical
                    stability, performance, and visualization require more
                    sophisticated interfaces and back-end libraries. For study,
                    exam preparation, or small engineering checks, 2×2–4×4 is
                    typically enough to illustrate the main ideas.
                  </div>
                </article>
